                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d801">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of the Central American Court
                            of Justice</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                        State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Jose</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-06-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 23, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Encouraged by the approval of your excellency’s Government in the matter of
                    mediation in Nicaragua the Central American court has insisted on it and
                    proposed practical means of pacification. American legation here will in due
                    course be informed of the bases.</p>
                <p>With respectful consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ernesto Martin</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
